      <section eId="sec_5615">
        <num>5615</num>
        <heading>Disposition upon appeal from order granting new trial or hearing</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_5615__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of\nsection 5601, or subparagraph (iii) of paragraph two of subdivision</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_5615__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\nof section 5602, the court of appeals shall affirm the order appealed\nfrom and shall render judgment or order absolute against the appellant\nunless the order or opinion of the appellate division recites either\nthat the questions of fact have not been considered or that the court\nhas considered the questions of fact and has determined that it would\nnot grant a new trial or hearing upon those questions.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
